oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Mr. and Mrs. Stanley R. Teachout with a group on a trip to the Petrified Forest, circa 1916
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A photographic postcard picturing a group of people at the Petrified Forest located in the Western United States, circa 1916. Elizabeth “Libbie” (Walsh) Teachout is pictured third from left, standing beside her husband Dr. Stanley R. Teachout, both of Nashville, Tennessee. Forms part of Mrs. Libbie (Walsh) Teachout Papers. 1 photographic postcard.
